Description: MariahCorp communities are both operational and financial efficiencies that allow for maximum profit potential.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Key in MariahCorp communities are both operational and financial efficiencies that allow for maximum profit potential as well as very attractive operational cost savings for both tenants and residents. MariahCorp communities also incorporate proprietary amenities and technologies not found in any other developments.    MariahCorp's current mission is to build one of the most advanced urban-style “city within a city” projects in all of the Americas. The project is a mix of 2 neighborhoods, one is BicksBurg Square and the other is Barnett Parke, combined to form an urban center containing 38 high rise structures with 12 million+ square feet of space. Consisting of residential apartments, condos, retail shops, office towers, entertainment venues and a hotel/convention center, the community will be home to 7,500 permanent residents and over 30,000 in additional daytime population. Automation, security and other advanced technologies provide an unparalleled experience, all situated at the foot of the 14,000-foot peaks of the majestic Colorado Rockies.     The community is self powered via both solar and geothermal energy. Average per-person water consumption and waste output is reduced by over 50% with absolutely no sacrifice in lifestyle quality. Residents and tenants can do without cars by using the community's automated transportation system, which also connects to the Denver Regional Transit System, providing easy access to all Colorado East Slope cities along a 90+ mile corridor. Mass transit is also available to the many world-class Colorado ski resorts located just 1 hour west of Denver. Additionally, Denver Int'l. Airport is just 15 minutes away.

Co-purchasing is permitted, providing flexibility for buyers with various financial arrangements​​. Furthermore, Acropolis Gardens is part of a larger complex consisting of 16 buildings, each with 5 stories, summing up to a total of 617 units. This expansive setup indicates the complex's capacity to accommodate a substantial number of residents, making it a significant residential hub in Astoria. The inclusion of guarantors in the leasing process is also a notable feature, providing additional flexibility for tenants​​. Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: 3 Monkeys Inflatables is a company specializing in bounce house and party rentals, primarily serving Central and Southern Pennsylvania and Maryland. The company also features larger attractions like mobile escape room rentals, rock walls, Euro bungee rentals, VR rentals, trackless train rentals, giant games, carnival games, portable zip line rentals, large carnival hard rides, and mobile mini golf rentals. The company prides itself on being a top choice for party rentals in the region, with over 20 years of experience. They emphasize quality, affordability, and exceptional customer service. Their team is trained in the safe setup of inflatable rentals and party equipment, prioritizing customer safety. 3 Monkeys Inflatables offers a comprehensive range of event rental options for both small backyard parties and large-scale events. In addition to their extensive rental options, the company ensures that all their units are insured, inspected, and cleaned daily with anti-microbial coatings for added safety. They have a strong focus on reliability, accuracy, and safety, making them a trusted choice for rental needs in their service area. The company also offers an easy online booking system for convenience. 3 Monkeys Inflatables has been in business since 2007 and serves a wide area in Pennsylvania and Maryland, including York, Lancaster, Harrisburg, and surrounding areas. They offer a variety of bounce houses, water slides, and party equipment rentals, catering to different types of events like birthday parties, corporate events, school and church events, and more.
